# UI Toolkit (not UGUI)

**Do not** use `com.unity.ugui`, Canvas, or `UnityEngine.UI` for new UI.

Stack: **UI Toolkit** + **UniRx** (`ReactiveProperty`, `ReactiveCommand`) + **UniTask** (async UI flows).

Bindings: `Assets/Game/UI/Runtime/Extensions/` — mirrors legacy UniRx/UniTask uGUI API on `UnityEngine.UIElements.*`.

## Folder layout

```
Assets/Game/UI/Runtime/
├── Bindings/       # UIBindingScope (required)
├── Extensions/     # UniRx + UniTask UITK bridge
├── Controllers/
├── ViewModels/
├── Views/
├── UXML/
└── USS/
```

PanelSettings: `Assets/Game/Settings/UI/`.

## MCP workflow (`manage_ui`)

When Unity Editor is connected — **MCP-first** (`unity-mcp.mdc`). Activate group **ui** before UI work.

1. `create` / `update` UXML and USS
2. `link_stylesheet` — wire USS to UXML (use `<ui:Style>`, not bare `<Style>`)
3. `attach_ui_document` — bind UXML to scene `UIDocument` (do not hand-edit `.unity` YAML)
4. `get_visual_tree` — verify resolved sizes/positions/colors
5. Play mode → `render_ui` — visual check (call twice in play mode for PNG)
6. Controllers / ViewModels — **MCP-first** (`create_script`, `apply_text_edits`); file tools only for large refactors or Editor offline

## Main menu (sample)

`MainMenu.unity` → `--- UI ---/MainMenu` with `MainMenuController`, `MainMenu.uxml`, `MainMenu.uss`.

| Piece | Role |
|-------|------|
| `MainMenuViewModel` | `PlayCommand`, `QuitCommand`, sound/volume reactive props |
| `MainMenuController` | Binds UI, fade-out on Play, keyboard shortcuts |
| `GameAudio` (`Game.Core`) | Global `AudioListener.volume` from menu toggles |
| `GameSession` (`Game.Core`) | `Begin()` when Play pressed; gameplay systems subscribe |
| `GameplayReveal` (`Game.Gameplay`) | Eases key light after `GameSession.Started` |

VFX sample prefab is **not** wired to the menu — reference only (`unity-vfx.mdc`).

## UIBindingScope (required)

Every screen with reactive bindings:

```csharp
_bindingScope = new UIBindingScope(rootVisualElement);
_bindingScope.Add(viewModel.Title.SubscribeToText(titleLabel));
_bindingScope.Add(viewModel.PlayCommand.BindTo(playButton));
// OnDestroy: _bindingScope.Dispose();
```

Scope also disposes on `DetachFromPanelEvent`. On dispose, only unregisters panel callbacks when `_root.panel != null`.

## UI callback lifecycle

Register transient UI callbacks in **`OnEnable`**, unregister in **`OnDisable`** — not in `OnDestroy` via `UIDocument.rootVisualElement` (null after panel detach → NRE).

```csharp
private VisualElement _root;

private void OnEnable()
{
    _root ??= _uiDocument.rootVisualElement;
    _root?.RegisterCallback<KeyDownEvent>(OnKeyDown);
}

private void OnDisable()
{
    _root?.UnregisterCallback<KeyDownEvent>(OnKeyDown);
}
```

## uGUI → UI Toolkit API map

| Legacy uGUI (removed) | UI Toolkit (use) |
|-----------------------|------------------|
| `Text` | `Label` / `TextElement` |
| `SubscribeToInteractable(Selectable)` | `SubscribeToEnabled(VisualElement)` |
| `InputField` | `TextField` |
| `Dropdown` (int index) | `DropdownField` + `OnIndexChangedAsObservable` |
| `ScrollRect` | `ScrollView` |

## Controller pattern

- **ViewModel:** `ReactiveProperty`, `ReactiveCommand` — no `VisualElement` references
- **Controller:** `[RequireComponent(typeof(UIDocument))]`, creates `UIBindingScope`, wires bindings
- Async scene load: `await SceneManager.LoadSceneAsync("Game").ToUniTask(cancellationToken)` from MainMenu Play
- MainMenu fades out in-place, then loads `Game.unity` (separate gameplay scene)
- **Mouse only:** `UiNavigationPolicy.ConfigureMouseOnly` on menu/HUD roots — no keyboard focus or WASD/arrow navigation

## UXML / USS

- Name elements for `root.Q<T>("Name")`
- USS variables on `:root`; hide with `display: none` or `.menu--hidden`
